From f0712f3193d353c56bebcded963cca04bef8210f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yi Ding <yi.s.ding@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 06:21:25 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 05/65] media: rockchip: mpp: clamp oversized register requests
 correctly

Plain-language impact:
Oversized register requests are now trimmed to the valid remaining range.

Kernel details:
mpp_check_req() assigned the overflow amount to req->size. The valid length is max_size - req_off.

Source: split from patches/cleanup-draft after docs/11-bsp-audit.md verification.
Signed-off-by: Yi Ding <yi.s.ding@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/video/rockchip/mpp/mpp_common.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/video/rockchip/mpp/mpp_common.c b/drivers/video/rockchip/mpp/mpp_common.c
index fd1f71c23eda..c9e45c162481 100644
--- a/drivers/video/rockchip/mpp/mpp_common.c
+++ b/drivers/video/rockchip/mpp/mpp_common.c
@@ -1966,7 +1966,7 @@ int mpp_check_req(struct mpp_request *req, int base,
 	if ((req_off + req->size) > max_size) {
 		mpp_err("error: req_off %x, req_size %x, max_size %x\n",
 			req_off, req->size, max_size);
-		req->size = req_off + req->size - max_size;
+		req->size = max_size - req_off;
 	}
 
 	return 0;
-- 
2.53.0

